one meter, one meter.

00:22:55.970 --> 00:22:57.410 align:middle line:90%
You're in a gravitational field.

00:22:57.410 --> 00:23:01.740 align:middle line:84%
Your head is actually moving
at a slightly faster rate

00:23:01.740 --> 00:23:02.540 align:middle line:90%
than your feet.

00:23:02.540 --> 00:23:04.707 align:middle line:84%
>> The second law of
thermodynamics says that things

00:23:04.707 --> 00:23:05.910 align:middle line:90%
unwind and move forward.

00:23:05.910 --> 00:23:08.300 align:middle line:90%
So that gives an era of time.

00:23:08.300 --> 00:23:10.910 align:middle line:84%
But at the quantum world,
in the micro world,

00:23:10.910 --> 00:23:13.280 align:middle line:84%
the second law of thermodynamics
doesn't seem to hold.

00:23:13.280 --> 00:23:15.620 align:middle line:84%
And things can go
backwards or be timeless.

00:23:15.620 --> 00:23:20.270 align:middle line:84%
>> The fundamental equations
of motion that we have,

00:23:20.270 --> 00:23:23.690 align:middle line:84%
both in classical mechanics
and in quantum mechanics,

00:23:23.690 --> 00:23:26.990 align:middle line:84%
have this property called
time reversal symmetry.

00:23:26.990 --> 00:23:30.950 align:middle line:84%
OK, there is a
certain way in which

00:23:30.950 --> 00:23:34.010 align:middle line:84%
they don't distinguish between
the past and the future.

00:23:34.010 --> 00:23:36.830 align:middle line:84%
Or to put it
slightly differently,

00:23:36.830 --> 00:23:41.060 align:middle line:84%
these equations entail that for
any process that's possible,

00:23:41.060 --> 00:23:44.202 align:middle line:84%
the same process happening
backwards is possible.

00:23:44.202 --> 00:23:45.660 align:middle line:84%
Now when I say
happening backwards,

00:23:45.660 --> 00:23:48.030 align:middle line:84%
I don't mean going
backwards in time.

00:23:48.030 --> 00:23:52.460 align:middle line:84%
I mean, as time goes forward,
the reverse sequence of things

00:23:52.460 --> 00:23:55.490 align:middle line:90%
happens, OK?

00:23:55.490 --> 00:23:57.590 align:middle line:90%
The world isn't like that.

00:23:57.590 --> 00:24:02.420 align:middle line:84%
There are all sorts of what
people refer to as time

00:24:02.420 --> 00:24:04.370 align:middle line:90%
asymmetries in the world.

00:24:04.370 --> 00:24:06.830 align:middle line:84%
And people usually
chop these asymmetries

00:24:06.830 --> 00:24:08.930 align:middle line:90%
up into three different levels.

00:24:08.930 --> 00:24:11.270 align:middle line:84%
Level one, there
are all sorts of

00:24:11.270 --> 00:24:13.280 align:middle line:90%
ordinary physical processes--

00:24:13.280 --> 00:24:16.580 align:middle line:84%
ice melting, smoke spreading
out in a room, people

00:24:16.580 --> 00:24:19.880 align:middle line:84%
getting wrinkly as they get
old, so on and so forth--

00:24:19.880 --> 00:24:23.160 align:middle line:84%
that we never see
happening in reverse.

00:24:23.160 --> 00:24:28.090 align:middle line:84%
Two, we have a very different
kind of epistemic access

00:24:28.090 --> 00:24:30.400 align:middle line:84%
to the past than we
do to the future.

00:24:30.400 --> 00:24:34.870 align:middle line:84%
That is that the ease with
which we can know things

00:24:34.870 --> 00:24:37.960 align:middle line:84%
about the past and the way in
which we come to know things

00:24:37.960 --> 00:24:41.410 align:middle line:84%
about the past and the detail
with which we can know things

00:24:41.410 --> 00:24:44.650 align:middle line:84%
about the past is utterly
different than the ease

00:24:44.650 --> 00:24:48.890 align:middle line:84%
and the access and the detail
that we have to the future.

00:24:48.890 --> 00:24:53.410 align:middle line:84%
Three, an asymmetry
of influence.

00:24:53.410 --> 00:24:58.720 align:middle line:84%
We have a very deep
conviction that by acting now,

00:24:58.720 --> 00:25:02.660 align:middle line:84%
we can affect the
future but not the past.

00:25:02.660 --> 00:25:07.030 align:middle line:84%
Given the complete time symmetry
of the fundamental equations

00:25:07.030 --> 00:25:10.540 align:middle line:84%
of motion, all of
these three asymmetries

00:25:10.540 --> 00:25:12.490 align:middle line:90%
are extremely mysterious.

00:25:12.490 --> 00:25:14.760 align:middle line:84%
And moreover,
they're asymmetries

00:25:14.760 --> 00:25:18.310 align:middle line:84%
that play an incredibly
fundamental role

00:25:18.310 --> 00:25:21.530 align:middle line:90%
in every second of our lives.

00:25:21.530 --> 00:25:27.010 align:middle line:84%
So that's been a puzzle hanging
over physics for a long time.

00:25:27.010 --> 00:25:29.950 align:middle line:84%
Where does this asymmetry
come from if not

00:25:29.950 --> 00:25:31.610 align:middle line:90%
the equations of motion?

00:25:31.610 --> 00:25:33.130 align:middle line:84%
The equations of
motion are supposed

00:25:33.130 --> 00:25:36.220 align:middle line:84%
to be the whole story
about how the world works.

00:25:36.220 --> 00:25:38.710 align:middle line:84%
But in that story,
these asymmetries

00:25:38.710 --> 00:25:40.480 align:middle line:90%
don't show up at all.

00:25:40.480 --> 00:25:45.040 align:middle line:84%
And yet, these asymmetries
are profound, ubiquitous,

00:25:45.040 --> 00:25:48.350 align:middle line:84%
inescapable features of
every second of our lives

00:25:48.350 --> 00:25:49.150 align:middle line:90%
in the world.

00:25:49.150 --> 00:25:52.235 align:middle line:84%
>> One of the most
unpalatable ideas still,

00:25:52.235 --> 00:25:54.610 align:middle line:84%
in spite of the fact that
quantum physics has been around

00:25:54.610 --> 00:25:59.440 align:middle line:84%
a long time, is the possibility
or the notion that the future

00:25:59.440 --> 00:26:03.100 align:middle line:84%
can have a causative
effect on the present.

00:26:03.100 --> 00:26:06.020 align:middle line:84%
We believe that the past
can have a causative effect

00:26:06.020 --> 00:26:06.820 align:middle line:90%
on the present.

00:26:06.820 --> 00:26:08.140 align:middle line:90%
I hold the ball.

00:26:08.140 --> 00:26:10.030 align:middle line:90%
I drop it, it falls.

00:26:10.030 --> 00:26:13.060 align:middle line:84%
Cause, effect-- when
it hits the ground.

00:26:13.060 --> 00:26:15.370 align:middle line:84%
But could the
ground be the cause

00:26:15.370 --> 00:26:17.835 align:middle line:84%
of my dropping the ball
in the first place?

00:26:17.835 --> 00:26:20.440 align:middle line:84%
>> It's only in conscious
experience that it seems that

00:26:20.440 --> 00:26:23.140 align:middle line:90%
we move forward in time.

00:26:23.140 --> 00:26:25.550 align:middle line:84%
In quantum theory, you can
also go backwards in time.

00:26:25.550 --> 00:26:27.550 align:middle line:84%
And there's some
suggestion that processes

00:26:27.550 --> 00:26:30.520 align:middle line:84%
in the brain related to
consciousness project backwards

00:26:30.520 --> 00:26:31.550 align:middle line:90%
in time.

00:26:31.550 --> 00:26:34.270 align:middle line:84%
For example, in the late
1970s a neurophysiologist

00:26:34.270 --> 00:26:36.630 align:middle line:84%
at University of
California San Francisco

00:26:36.630 --> 00:26:40.360 align:middle line:84%
named Ben Libet did some
very famous experiments.

00:26:40.360 --> 00:26:43.300 align:middle line:84%
What Libet did
was study patients

00:26:43.300 --> 00:26:46.140 align:middle line:84%
who were having neurosurgery
on their brains,

00:26:46.140 --> 00:26:48.753 align:middle line:84%
with their brains exposed,
while they were awake.

00:26:48.753 --> 00:26:50.170 align:middle line:84%
They were given a
local anesthetic

00:26:50.170 --> 00:26:52.300 align:middle line:84%
to numb the area of
the skull and scalp

00:26:52.300 --> 00:26:53.760 align:middle line:90%
to access their brains.

00:26:53.760 --> 00:26:57.080 align:middle line:84%
And they were awake, and Ben
would talk to these people.

00:26:57.080 --> 00:27:00.790 align:middle line:84%
So for example, what he did was
stimulate their little finger

00:27:00.790 --> 00:27:03.280 align:middle line:84%
and look at the part
of the sensory cortex

00:27:03.280 --> 00:27:06.010 align:middle line:84%
on the opposite side
that was related to that,

00:27:06.010 --> 00:27:08.380 align:middle line:84%
record from it electrically,
and ask the patient

00:27:08.380 --> 00:27:11.710 align:middle line:84%
when he or she felt the
stimulus on the little finger.

00:27:11.710 --> 00:27:15.610 align:middle line:84%
And he would also stimulate at
that particular area of cortex.

00:27:15.610 --> 00:27:17.470 align:middle line:84%
Now what you would
think would be

00:27:17.470 --> 00:27:19.180 align:middle line:84%
that if you stimulate
the little finger,

00:27:19.180 --> 00:27:21.700 align:middle line:84%
it takes a finite period of
time to get to the opposite side

00:27:21.700 --> 00:27:22.910 align:middle line:90%
of the cortex.

00:27:22.910 --> 00:27:25.270 align:middle line:84%
So the patient would report
it a fraction of a second

00:27:25.270 --> 00:27:27.135 align:middle line:90%
later after the stimulus.

00:27:27.135 --> 00:27:28.510 align:middle line:84%
And when you
stimulated directly,

00:27:28.510 --> 00:27:31.270 align:middle line:84%
the patient would
report it immediately.

00:27:31.270 --> 00:27:32.960 align:middle line:90%
He found just the opposite.

00:27:32.960 --> 00:27:34.690 align:middle line:84%
When you stimulated
the little finger,

00:27:34.690 --> 00:27:36.610 align:middle line:90%
the patient felt it immediately.

00:27:36.610 --> 00:27:39.040 align:middle line:84%
And when he stimulated
directly on the cortex,

00:27:39.040 --> 00:27:40.473 align:middle line:90%
there was a delay.

00:27:40.473 --> 00:27:41.890 align:middle line:84%
After sorting
through all the data

00:27:41.890 --> 00:27:43.755 align:middle line:84%
and repeating this
over and over,

00:27:43.755 --> 00:27:45.880 align:middle line:84%
Libet came to the conclusion
that somehow the brain

00:27:45.880 --> 00:27:48.910 align:middle line:84%
was projecting information
backwards in time.

00:27:48.910 --> 00:27:50.800 align:middle line:84%
So it did take a
finite amount of time

00:27:50.800 --> 00:27:52.780 align:middle line:84%
to get to the sensory
cortex, but the brain

00:27:52.780 --> 00:27:54.970 align:middle line:84%
projected it
backwards in time so

00:27:54.970 --> 00:27:56.440 align:middle line:84%
that the conscious
perception was

00:27:56.440 --> 00:28:00.340 align:middle line:84%
that the stimulus was felt when
the pinch actually occurred.

00:28:00.340 --> 00:28:02.770 align:middle line:84%
>> There have been some studies
which have shown that when

00:28:02.770 --> 00:28:06.460 align:middle line:84%
people are beginning to move
a hand or beginning to say

00:28:06.460 --> 00:28:08.810 align:middle line:84%
something, there's actually
activity in the brain

00:28:08.810 --> 00:28:10.570 align:middle line:84%
in certain nerve
cells of the brain,

00:28:10.570 --> 00:28:12.940 align:middle line:84%
even before they become
consciously aware of what

00:28:12.940 --> 00:28:13.900 align:middle line:90%
they're trying to do.

00:28:13.900 --> 00:28:20.110 align:middle line:84%
>> In baseball, scientists
showed that if you study how

00:28:20.110 --> 00:28:23.290 align:middle line:84%
a batter can hit a pitch
coming at 100 miles an hour--

00:28:23.290 --> 00:28:26.350 align:middle line:84%
considering the recognition,
the visual processing,

00:28:26.350 --> 00:28:29.980 align:middle line:84%
the motor response, the
reflexes, synaptic delays--

00:28:29.980 --> 00:28:31.180 align:middle line:90%
it's impossible.

00:28:31.180 --> 00:28:33.760 align:middle line:90%
That was his conclusion.

00:28:33.760 --> 00:28:35.770 align:middle line:90%
How could it be accomplished?

00:28:35.770 --> 00:28:38.740 align:middle line:84%
Well, one possibility is that
as the batter is standing there,

00:28:38.740 --> 00:28:41.530 align:middle line:84%
the ball comes across
the plate and the batter

00:28:41.530 --> 00:28:44.590 align:middle line:84%
sees where the ball is,
recognizes it, and decides

00:28:44.590 --> 00:28:46.290 align:middle line:84%
where to swing by
the time the ball

00:28:46.290 --> 00:28:48.890 align:middle line:84%
is already in the
catcher's mitt.

00:28:48.890 --> 00:28:51.350 align:middle line:84%
But the information is
projected backwards in time

00:28:51.350 --> 00:28:55.390 align:middle line:84%
so that he or she swings
at the previous time

00:28:55.390 --> 00:28:57.580 align:middle line:84%
when the ball is just
coming across the plate.

00:28:57.580 --> 00:28:59.890 align:middle line:84%
This could be
happening all the time

00:28:59.890 --> 00:29:01.863 align:middle line:84%
in our normal everyday
consciousness.

00:29:01.863 --> 00:29:03.280 align:middle line:84%
And there's some
other experiments

00:29:03.280 --> 00:29:04.155 align:middle line:90%
that have shown this.

00:29:04.155 --> 00:29:06.790 align:middle line:84%
Dick Berman and Dean Radin
have done some experiments

00:29:06.790 --> 00:29:09.970 align:middle line:84%
where a subject sits
at a computer screen

00:29:09.970 --> 00:29:13.360 align:middle line:84%
and watches a series of images,
which may be somewhat bland

00:29:13.360 --> 00:29:16.390 align:middle line:84%
or may have highly
emotional content.

00:29:16.390 --> 00:29:20.050 align:middle line:84%
And they just study their
galvanic skin response

00:29:20.050 --> 00:29:22.450 align:middle line:90%
as a means of emotion.

00:29:22.450 --> 00:29:25.043 align:middle line:84%
And they vary the timing of when
the pictures going to occur.

00:29:25.043 --> 00:29:26.710 align:middle line:84%
So the subject doesn't
know exactly when

00:29:26.710 --> 00:29:27.760 align:middle line:90%
it's going to occur.

00:29:27.760 --> 00:29:30.190 align:middle line:84%
What they find is
that, not surprisingly,

00:29:30.190 --> 00:29:34.060 align:middle line:84%
the emotional pictures give
a much greater response.

00:29:34.060 --> 00:29:36.910 align:middle line:84%
But both the emotional and
the unemotional responses

00:29:36.910 --> 00:29:38.830 align:middle line:84%
show up a half a
second to two seconds

00:29:38.830 --> 00:29:41.980 align:middle line:84%
before the stimulus actually
occurs on the screen.

00:29:41.980 --> 00:29:45.790 align:middle line:84%
And a fellow named Chester
Wiley replicated this, not only

00:29:45.790 --> 00:29:47.590 align:middle line:90%
in humans but in worms.

00:29:47.590 --> 00:29:51.460 align:middle line:84%
So this may be possibly a
very widespread phenomenon

00:29:51.460 --> 00:29:53.290 align:middle line:90%
of backwards projection in time.

00:29:53.290 --> 00:29:55.540 align:middle line:84%
The only explanation is
through quantum physics.

00:29:55.540 --> 00:30:00.730 align:middle line:84%
>> Pat Price was a
fantastic remote viewer.

00:30:00.730 --> 00:30:04.330 align:middle line:84%
And he was supposed to
draw where his traveler was

00:30:04.330 --> 00:30:05.290 align:middle line:90%
going, as usual.

00:30:05.290 --> 00:30:09.040 align:middle line:84%
And he drew two tanks
and a swimming pool.

00:30:09.040 --> 00:30:11.980 align:middle line:84%
And when the investigators
looked at it,

00:30:11.980 --> 00:30:14.740 align:middle line:84%
the scientist said Pat
must've just got it

00:30:14.740 --> 00:30:17.460 align:middle line:84%
wrong this time, because he was
right about the swimming pool.

00:30:17.460 --> 00:30:19.270 align:middle line:84%
They had sent their
traveling partner

00:30:19.270 --> 00:30:22.600 align:middle line:84%
to the municipal swimming
pool in Palo Alto.

00:30:22.600 --> 00:30:25.480 align:middle line:84%
And they said Pat just
got it wrong this time.

00:30:25.480 --> 00:30:29.470 align:middle line:84%
Months later, one
of the scientists

00:30:29.470 --> 00:30:33.970 align:middle line:84%
received something from the
Palo Alto Chamber of Commerce.

00:30:33.970 --> 00:30:37.120 align:middle line:84%
And it had images of
the municipal swimming

00:30:37.120 --> 00:30:39.220 align:middle line:90%
pool 50 years earlier.

00:30:39.220 --> 00:30:41.920 align:middle line:84%
And what they saw was
the swimming pool,

00:30:41.920 --> 00:30:45.890 align:middle line:84%
but two tanks exactly
where Pat had drawn them.

00:30:45.890 --> 00:30:49.030 align:middle line:84%
And so what Pat's
mind had done was not

00:30:49.030 --> 00:30:53.740 align:middle line:84%
to see what the swimming
pool was in present time.

00:30:53.740 --> 00:30:56.015 align:middle line:84%
He saw it back as
it was 50 years ago.

00:30:56.015 --> 00:30:58.640 align:middle line:84%
>> I know it seems to me that I
often do things and then decide

00:30:58.640 --> 00:31:00.070 align:middle line:84%
a fraction of a second
later what to do.

00:31:00.070 --> 00:31:01.195 align:middle line:90%
But I've already done that.

00:31:01.195 --> 00:31:04.540 align:middle line:84%
>> We're beginning to see
that even time itself is not

00:31:04.540 --> 00:31:05.680 align:middle line:90%
sacrosanct.

00:31:05.680 --> 00:31:09.250 align:middle line:84%
We're allowed now to get
into it in a different way.

00:31:09.250 --> 00:31:14.150 align:middle line:84%
David Deutsch, Oxford physics
professor, was, I think,

00:31:14.150 --> 00:31:16.550 align:middle line:84%
one of the prime inventors
of quantum computation,

00:31:16.550 --> 00:31:17.770 align:middle line:90%
the quantum computer.

00:31:17.770 --> 00:31:21.250 align:middle line:84%
And he is very much into
parallel universes and time

00:31:21.250 --> 00:31:23.910 align:middle line:84%
travel and says all the
paradoxes now of time travel.

00:31:23.910 --> 00:31:25.390 align:middle line:84%
You can go backwards
and farther.

00:31:25.390 --> 00:31:27.850 align:middle line:84%
Go backwards in time and knock
off your father and mother

00:31:27.850 --> 00:31:29.440 align:middle line:84%
before they have
you and come back,

00:31:29.440 --> 00:31:31.840 align:middle line:84%
and you're still
alive and no paradox.

00:31:31.840 --> 00:31:34.120 align:middle line:84%
And even to explain
that is difficult to do,

00:31:34.120 --> 00:31:36.950 align:middle line:84%
but nevertheless, put them
in a parallel universe

00:31:36.950 --> 00:31:38.147 align:middle line:90%
and it's no problem.

00:31:38.147 --> 00:31:39.730 align:middle line:84%
So these are the
kinds of things we're

00:31:39.730 --> 00:31:40.690 align:middle line:90%
doing in physics right now.

00:31:40.690 --> 00:31:41.490 align:middle line:90%
We're thinking.

00:31:41.490 --> 00:31:42.910 align:middle line:90%
We're rethinking time.

00:31:42.910 --> 00:31:45.700 align:middle line:84%
And it may very well
be that the next phase

00:31:45.700 --> 00:31:48.310 align:middle line:84%
of time travel in
a physical device

00:31:48.310 --> 00:31:50.890 align:middle line:84%
may be in the next 50
to 100 years from now.

00:31:50.890 --> 00:31:55.420 align:middle line:84%
>> Science suggests to us that
parallel universes are living

00:31:55.420 --> 00:32:00.280 align:middle line:84%
simultaneously, that we're
living 100,000 lives or five

00:32:00.280 --> 00:32:02.710 align:middle line:84%
lives-- you know, however
much you can handle--

00:32:02.710 --> 00:32:05.920 align:middle line:84%
simultaneously, and that
all the things that we do

00:32:05.920 --> 00:32:07.892 align:middle line:90%
are at work right now.

00:32:07.892 --> 00:32:08.720 align:middle line:90%
>> I'll be late.

00:32:08.720 --> 00:32:11.800 align:middle line:84%
>> You can always
go back in time.

00:32:11.800 --> 00:32:13.712 align:middle line:90%
[DISTANT CHEERING]

00:32:13.712 --> 00:32:16.580 align:middle line:90%
[BUZZER]

00:32:16.580 --> 00:32:17.536 align:middle line:90%


00:32:17.536 --> 00:32:19.450 align:middle line:90%
What's the matter?

00:32:19.450 --> 00:32:22.588 align:middle line:90%
Remember, it's empty.

00:32:22.588 --> 00:32:25.990 align:middle line:90%
>> How do you know this shit?

00:32:25.990 --> 00:32:28.588 align:middle line:90%
>> I read "Dr. Quantum" comics.

00:32:28.588 --> 00:32:31.130 align:middle line:84%
Everybody thinks it's just kid's
stuff, but I know it's real.

00:32:31.130 --> 00:32:34.356 align:middle line:84%
It's how I do my
magic on the court.

00:32:34.356 --> 00:32:35.550 align:middle line:90%
>> Yo!

00:32:35.550 --> 00:32:38.580 align:middle line:84%
What they taught us in
school isn't really the way

00:32:38.580 --> 00:32:43.710 align:middle line:84%
it is, and our senses
are playing tricks on us.

00:32:43.710 --> 00:32:47.280 align:middle line:84%
We've just got to wonder,
what is this reality that we

00:32:47.280 --> 00:32:49.500 align:middle line:90%
find ourselves in?

00:32:49.500 --> 00:32:53.870 align:middle line:84%
Quantum physics says it's all
just waves of information.

